<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Engine Electrical - Electronic
        Control Module (ECM) - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="5">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To install the ECM and support assembly
                <emph type="bold">as one unit</emph>, perform the following steps:
            </para>
            <figure id="f1201012" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg6/EG6971.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>ECM Support Assembly Bushings and Pins</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Top Bushing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bushing Pin</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bottom Bushing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bottom Mounting Bracket</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">If previously removed, install the bushings and pins in the bolt holes of the support
                    assembly.
                </para>
                <figure id="f2051002" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figeg9/EG9138.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                    <caption>ECM Support Assembly Upper Mounting Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install the ECM and support assembly on the engine. Install and tighten the two upper
                    mounting bolts to the special torque value.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1201093" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figeg6/EG6970.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>ECM Support Assembly Lower Mounting Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install and tighten the two lower mounting bolts to the special torque value.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201018" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg7/EG7410.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>ECM Wiring Harnesses and Mounting Bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connector Bolt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Engine Wiring Harness</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">ECM Mounting Bolt (4)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To install the support assembly and ECM
                <emph type="bold">separately</emph>, first perform the procedure in Step 1 for the support assembly
                only. Then install the ECM on the support assembly. Install and tighten the four mounting bolts to the
                special torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the engine wiring harness to the ECM. Tighten the connector bolt to the special
                torque value.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201020" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg6/EG6974.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Glow Plug Relay</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Glow Plug Connector Terminals</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Battery Connection Terminal</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the battery and glow plug connectors to the glow plug relay terminals.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
